==English==

===Adjective===
'''lamellate'''

#Having at least some component segments being lengthened on one side and flattened into circles, making these segments look like a stack of dinner plates.
#:''The dung beetle had '''lamellate''' [[antenna]]e.''

===Usage note===
This term is used especially to describe certain insect antennae in which the last segments are so shaped into a compact club of flat plates.